name: Michael Galero
text: Skimmed through this study:      http://www.iea.org/publications/freepublications/publication/SoutheastAsiaEnergyOutlook_WEO2013SpecialReport.pdf    I noticed that Philippines doesn't produce as much energy resources as its neighbors, whether oil, gas or coal production. Couple that with the fact that our exchange rate favors exporters over importers, and you have what the industry calls a double whammy.
